ZH: 下游是指河流或水域的末端部分。
EN: The downstream refers to the lower part of a river or water body.
ZH: 他们建了一座大坝，以防止洪水影响下游地区。
EN: They built a dam to prevent floods from affecting the downstream area.
ZH: 这条河支流的下游有许多漂亮的风景。
EN: There are many beautiful landscapes downstream of this river tributary.
ZH: 下游的鱼类数量通常相对较多。
EN: The number of fish is usually higher downstream.
ZH: 下游地区是这个城市的供水来源。
EN: The downstream area is the water source of this city.
ZH: 我们计划在下游修建一个水电站。
EN: We plan to build a hydroelectric power station downstream.
